The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing multi-echo magnetic resonance images using compressed sensing techniques. The use of structured deep dictionaries for adaptive reconstruction is the main focus of the paper, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of partial K-space scans and structured CS algorithms, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on real datasets, which suggests that numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category may also be relevant.
